  "texts": [
    "The judge achieved 98.2% recall and 94.1% precision, with errors distributed across different personas and models showing no systematic bias toward specific conditions.To ensure the conclusions are robust to judge measurement error, the uncertainty in the judge's false positive and false negative rates was modeled using Bayesian inference (see Appendix H).",
    "This uncertainty was then propagated through the Rogan-Gladen correction estimator [34] to generate credible intervals for key findings.",
    "This simulation-based approach distinguishes itself from both frequentist adjustment methods [19] and full MCMC prevalence models [13].",
    "Key findings remained robust: the Financial Advisor versus Neurosurgeon difference at Prompt 1 was 30.2 percentage points [95% CI: 24.1, 33.7], and model heterogeneity was 73.0 percentage points [95% CI: 70.2, 76.5].",
    "1 Model SelectionSixteen open-weight models available through the DeepInfra API were selected to represent diverse parameter scales and training approaches across major open weight model families."
